            <abstract>
<p>In the Ethiopian tradition there are two texts referred to as "The Book which Came from Jerusalem". One of them (<ref type="work" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT3843BookTh">CAe 3843</ref>) is transmitted
as part of the <ref type="work" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT1931Mashaf">Maṣḥafa Gǝnzat</ref>. The other (the present record) is included in some manuscripts
 of <ref type="work" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT1295Dersan">Dǝrsāna Mikāʾel</ref> and rarely also in the <ref type="work" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT2222RetuaH">Rǝtuʿa Hāymānot homiliary</ref>.</p>
            </abstract>
